To find (A × B) ∪ (A × {5}), we first need to find the Cartesian products A × B and A × {5}.

A × B = {(a, b) | a ∈ A, b ∈ B} = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4)}

A × {5} = {(a, b) | a ∈ A, b ∈ {5}} = {(1, 5), (2, 5)}

Now, we find the union of these two sets:

(A × B) ∪ (A × {5}) = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4), (1, 5), (2, 5)}
